<p>Less seriously, and also from <em>Hollow Knight</em>,</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Water is refreshing, but if you try to breathe it you are in for a nasty shock.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>- Zote the Mighty, Precept 44, “You Can Not Breathe Water”</p>
<p>More seriously,</p>
<blockquote>
<p>These petals&#8230; so white. Can you see them too&#8230; watching me from wherever you are?<br />
Perhaps dreams aren't such bad things after all&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>- Elderbug’s inner monologue</p>
<p>Context (some spoilers):</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This is the Dream Nail (lets you read minds and accrue extra SOUL (mana equivalent), as well as bust ghosts and invade dreams) monologue for Elderbug (first NPC encountered in-game, in Dirtmouth), after you give him a Delicate Flower (quest item to be delivered over the course of a grueling no-hit trek across Hallownest (setting of <em>Hollow Knight</em>) to the Traitor Lord’s Daughter’s grave in order to help the Grey Mourner move on and get a Mask Shard (Piece of Heart equivalent)). Elderbug is surprised and grateful as a result of this action, now having a lighter outlook on life. Arguably one of the most heartwarming things you can do in <em>Hollow Knight</em>.</p>
</div>
</div>
